{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.30",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 30 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:1",
      "text": "“But now those who are younger than I have me in derision, whose fathers I considered unworthy to put with my sheep dogs.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:2",
      "text": "Of what use is the strength of their hands to me, men in whom ripe age has perished?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:3",
      "text": "They are gaunt from lack and famine. They gnaw the dry ground, in the gloom of waste and desolation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:4",
      "text": "They pluck salt herbs by the bushes. The roots of the broom tree are their food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:5",
      "text": "They are driven out from among men. They cry after them as after a thief,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:6",
      "text": "so that they live in frightful valleys, and in holes of the earth and of the rocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:7",
      "text": "They bray among the bushes. They are gathered together under the nettles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:8",
      "text": "They are children of fools, yes, children of wicked men. They were flogged out of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:9",
      "text": "“Now I have become their song. Yes, I am a byword to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:10",
      "text": "They abhor me, they stand aloof from me, and don’t hesitate to spit in my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:11",
      "text": "For he has untied his cord, and afflicted me; and they have thrown off restraint before me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:12",
      "text": "On my right hand rise the rabble. They thrust aside my feet. They cast their ways of destruction up against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:13",
      "text": "They mar my path. They promote my destruction without anyone’s help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:14",
      "text": "As through a wide breach they come. They roll themselves in amid the ruin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:15",
      "text": "Terrors have turned on me. They chase my honor as the wind. My welfare has passed away as a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:16",
      "text": "“Now my soul is poured out within me. Days of affliction have taken hold of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:17",
      "text": "In the night season my bones are pierced in me, and the pains that gnaw me take no rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:18",
      "text": "My garment is disfigured by great force. It binds me about as the collar of my tunic.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:19",
      "text": "He has cast me into the mire. I have become like dust and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:20",
      "text": "I cry to you, and you do not answer me. I stand up, and you gaze at me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:21",
      "text": "You have turned to be cruel to me. With the might of your hand you persecute me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:22",
      "text": "You lift me up to the wind, and drive me with it. You dissolve me in the storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:23",
      "text": "For I know that you will bring me to death, to the house appointed for all living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:24",
      "text": "“However doesn’t one stretch out a hand in his fall? Or in his calamity therefore cry for help?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:25",
      "text": "Didn’t I weep for him who was in trouble? Wasn’t my soul grieved for the needy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:26",
      "text": "When I looked for good, then evil came. When I waited for light, darkness came.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:27",
      "text": "My heart is troubled, and doesn’t rest. Days of affliction have come on me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:28",
      "text": "I go mourning without the sun. I stand up in the assembly, and cry for help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:29",
      "text": "I am a brother to jackals, and a companion to ostriches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:30",
      "text": "My skin grows black and peels from me. My bones are burned with heat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.30.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:31",
      "text": "Therefore my harp has turned to mourning, and my pipe into the voice of those who weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
